<subSubSection id="4916A96F1AF4E35741967E6A4E432667" pageId="444" pageNumber="445" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8E6FC30ED3EA0264DD8F1CB36A92741E" pageId="444" pageNumber="445">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="533E77928561EC5D86D3090952B5FDAB" LSID="9B12D9E3-30A3-6A19-F220-3FC7DA68E1BF" authority="LeConte, 1852" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pericompsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pericompsus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="444" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pericompsus LeConte, 1852</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CEEB4A274B43FE2AA15D741974488853" pageId="444" pageNumber="445" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="237E0BEF9B463DC42059DD2622BFAC02" pageId="444" pageNumber="445">
<taxonomicName id="43C2082C13D8630342878A0D00543F26" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pericompsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="444" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pericompsus</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1852a: 191. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="662D56CF33FC0133810C8CB0000F4838" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="444" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ephippiatum">
<emphasis id="038601529087AB720C0BFF5FF407A30E" italics="true" pageId="444" pageNumber="445">Bembidium ephippiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Say, 1830 designated by LeConte (1859e: 553). Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis id="6CAD6B717989B48495EEF5D4DD644407" italics="true" pageId="444" pageNumber="445">peri</emphasis>
(very) and 
<emphasis id="5742D5CFC4327FCF607A49F927D9C8B7" italics="true" pageId="444" pageNumber="445">compsos</emphasis>
(elegant), probably alluding to the nice color of the body of adults of the three species LeConte had before him [masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F743634909F2BAE83B71AFE1A3A9D3BD" pageId="444" pageNumber="445" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="09D1BD6B9041DB4C6E73E9909FA5F408" pageId="444" pageNumber="445">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3852F0B28D13807E9438751AF94EFEEF" pageId="444" pageNumber="445">
New World, with about 70 species arrayed in three subgenera: 
<taxonomicName id="3552C7863485FC7BE73632169B25B2EA" authorityName="Erwin" authorityYear="1974" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Eidocompsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="444" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="47E82B0BE5E554DA69807B8FD299E7B7" italics="true" pageId="444" pageNumber="445">Eidocompsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Erwin (13 Neotropical species), 
<taxonomicName id="62D6CD6F93708A9F7707E5443FF39935" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pericompsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="444" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="76EE2419AFA3250D8AAFECB0A917AC06" italics="true" pageId="444" pageNumber="445">Pericompsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.str. (about 45 species), and 
<taxonomicName id="F74DFD74B7789138DE95109DDBE8235E" authorityName="Erwin" authorityYear="1974" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Upocompsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="444" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C33244102CBF6EDCAAF2A4EC8E20A604" italics="true" pageId="444" pageNumber="445">Upocompsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Erwin (nine Australian species).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9C084ABDD75A2FF4BD3D559AE126083D" pageId="444" pageNumber="445" type="identification">
<paragraph id="9AB27E339049FB0916F7555FF8FD53CD" pageId="444" pageNumber="445">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A964FFB749B32B615670BBF1B53A0EFF" pageId="444" pageNumber="445">Erwin (1974b) revised the species and provided a key for their identification.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
